		<step>Combine the [allspice|2.1], [thyme|3.1], [sugar|4.1], [sage|5.1], [nutmeg|6.1] [cinnamon|7.1] and [cayenne pepper|8.1] into a large bowl. In a separate bowl, stir together the [vinegar|9.1], [orange juice|13.1], [olive oil|11.1], [soy sauce|12.1], and [lime juice|14.1].</step>
		<step>Slowly whisk the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients until smooth. Mix in [spring onions|15.1], [white onions|16.1] and [garlic|17.1], then add the [chicken breasts|1.1] into the bowl, turning over to cover completely in the marinade. Cover and refrigerate for at least one hour, and up to overnight.</step>
		<step>Grill chicken for 4-5 minutes per side, brushing the marinade over while grilling. When no longer pink in the middle, remove to a plate, and let rest for 5 minutes. Slice and serve with your favorite BBQ or hot sauce.</step>
